OL,3,CBBC launches investigation into
OL,4,CStrictly stars' 'cocaine use'
OL,6,FAccording to reports, the allegations
OL,7,Fwere made in a legal submission by law
OL,8,Ffirm Russells in March on behalf of
OL,9,Fformer contestant Wynne Evans, who was
OL,10,Fdropped by the BBC after apologising
OL,11,Ffor using "inappropriate language"
OL,12,Fduring the launch of the Strictly tour.
OL,14,FOthers have also reported drug use on
OL,15,Fthe show.
OL,17,FA BBC spokesperson said: "We have
OL,18,Fclear protocols and policies in place
OL,19,Ffor dealing with any serious complaint
OL,20,Fraised with us.
